.TH "iso_packets_buffer_init" 9 "iso_packets_buffer_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iso_packets_buffer_init \- allocates the memory for packets
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" iso_packets_buffer_init
.BI "(struct iso_packets_buffer *b "  ","
.BI "struct fw_unit *unit "  ","
.BI "unsigned int count "  ","
.BI "unsigned int packet_size "  ","
.BI "enum dma_data_direction direction "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "b" 12
the buffer structure to initialize
.IP "unit" 12
the device at the other end of the stream
.IP "count" 12
the number of packets
.IP "packet_size" 12
the (maximum) size of a packet, in bytes
.IP "direction" 12
DMA_TO_DEVICE or DMA_FROM_DEVICE
